real_commentary: Some thoughts from Senior Reporter Ben Knapton... "Unlike the semi-final, this has been a much more tentative start from the Three Lions, who have conceded the lion's share of possession to Spain, albeit while defending resolutely - John Stones and Declan Rice have done their bits to snuff out attacks. While Nico Williams is looking lively on the left, Lamine Yamal is yet to get the better of Luke Shaw, making his first England start in over 12 months. Southgate's risky call is paying off so far, but this one is still waiting to explode into life."
